  "prompt": "What are some suggested heart touching (English) love songs?",
  "response": "Okay, here are some heart-touching love songs, broken down by vibe, with a mix of classics and more modern options:\n\n**For Deep, Soulful, and Timeless Love:**\n\n*   **\"At Last\" - Etta James:**  A classic for a reason.  It perfectly captures the feeling of finally finding the love you've been waiting for.\n*   **\"The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face\" - Roberta Flack:**  Simple, pure, and devastatingly beautiful in its depiction of love at first sight.\n*   **\"Wonderful World\" - Louis Armstrong:** A reminder that love makes the everyday world seem magical.\n*   **\"Hallelujah\" - Leonard Cohen (Various covers, Jeff Buckley is popular):** While not explicitly *just* a love song, the themes of love, loss, and redemption run deep.  It can be incredibly moving in a romantic context.\n*   **\"Can't Help Falling in Love\" - Elvis Presley:** Sweet, gentle, and speaks to the undeniable pull of love.\n*   **\"A Thousand Years\" - Christina Perri:**  A more modern classic, popular for weddings, about loving someone through eternity.\n\n**For Vulnerable, Honest, and Raw Love:**\n\n*   **\"Skinny Love\" - Bon Iver:**  A painfully beautiful song about a love that's falling apart, but still deeply felt.\n*   **\"Fix You\" - Coldplay:**  About supporting someone you love through hard times, and offering comfort.\n*   **\"Someone Like You\" - Adele:**  Bittersweet and relatable, about coming to terms with a lost love.\n*   **\"All of Me\" - John Legend:**  An honest and heartfelt declaration of accepting someone, flaws and all.\n*    **\"Say You Won't Let Go\" - James Arthur:**  A modern love song about wanting to hold onto someone forever.\n*    **\"Perfect\" - Ed Sheeran:** About a relatable, lasting love that may not always be perfect, but it is special.\n\n**For Sweet, Tender, and Romantic Love:**\n\n*   **\"The Way You Look Tonight\" - Frank Sinatra:**  Pure romance and admiration.\n*   **\"Come Away With Me\" - Norah Jones:**  Intimate and inviting, perfect for a quiet evening.\n*   **\"You Are The Best Thing\" - Ray LaMontagne:**  A soulful and joyful expression of gratitude for having someone special in your life.\n*   **\"La Vie en Rose\" - Edith Piaf (Many covers, including Louis Armstrong):** Although French, many English versions perfectly capture the feeling of seeing the world through rose-colored glasses because of love.\n*    **\"Thinking Out Loud\" - Ed Sheeran:**  About loving someone through the aging process and keeping it simple.\n\n**For Longing, Distance, and Unrequited Love:**\n\n*   **\"Hallelujah\" - Jeff Buckley:** (Mentioned above, but very appropriate here too)\n*   **\"I Will Always Love You\" - Dolly Parton (also Whitney Houston):** A powerful ballad about letting go of someone you love.\n*   **\"The Scientist\" - Coldplay:**  About wanting to go back in time to fix a relationship.\n*   **\"Someone to Watch Over Me\" - Ella Fitzgerald (and many others):**  A longing for someone to love and care for you.\n*   **\"Unchained Melody\" - The Righteous Brothers:**  Classic song of love and longing for the one you are separated from.\n*   **\"Hello\" - Adele:**  Powerful song of longing and reaching out to an old love.\n\n**Tips for Choosing:**\n\n*   **Consider the recipient:**  What kind of music do they usually enjoy? What message do you want to send?\n*   **Listen to the lyrics:**  Make sure the words resonate with your feelings and the situation.\n*   **Think about the melody:**  Does it evoke the right emotion?\n*   **Don't be afraid to go with your gut:**  Sometimes, the perfect song is simply the one that moves you the most.\n\nI hope this list gives you a good starting point! Good luck finding the perfect song!\n",
